  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Winterization Assistance for vulnerable populations in Logar and Paktya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Thanks to its vast experience, the IRC is uniquely positioned to provide seasonal winterization support to IDPs and refugee households. The IRC aims to build upon the already planned assistance under another emergency grant to expand its winterization coverage in Logar and Paktia. The proposed provinces are susceptible to extreme cold temperatures, high snowfall, and early onset of winter for longer periods of time than other provinces in Afghanistan. Thus, as per ES/NFI cluster winterization standards, through the AHF 5th Reserve Allocation, the IRC will aim to expand its winterization targets to the mentioned provinces in order support IDPs and refugee families to receive assistance for 4 months. The assistance, which will benefit 518 households, will be provided through unconditional, unrestricted cash ($260 USD, 19,500 AFN) in accordance with ES/NFI cluster standards.

PDM findings from previous AHF Reserve allocations for similar types of assistance show a strong acceptance of cash as a means of winterization assistance, households will make their own determinations based on their own needs. This project will have a direct impact on reducing protection risks associated with harmful coping mechanisms, including child protection risks, in IDP settlements and displacement areas. IRC will mainstream protection throughout project implementation to prioritize safety and dignity, and avoid causing harm, and to ensure meaningful access and accountability to affected populations.</narrative>
  </description>
